An Act relative to harassment prevention orders.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 258E of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
2 Section 12 the following new sections:
3 Section 13. If a plaintiff’s physical condition may prevent them from appearing in court,
4 either permanently or within the ten court business days in which the hearing after notice will
5 occur, the court, in its discretion, may conduct the hearing by speakerphone or video. The court
6 should conduct the hearing in the courtroom so that the hearing will be recorded.
7 Section 14. If in-hand service cannot be made because of lack of knowledge of the
8 defendant’s whereabouts, evidence that the defendant is avoiding service, or for any other
9 reason, a judge, upon finding that the appropriate law enforcement agency has made a
10 conscientious and reasonable effort to effect service, but has nevertheless failed, can authorize
11 service by alternative means.
